{#
  Cookie banner — the core of this demo.

  HOW IT WORKS WITHOUT JAVASCRIPT (progressive enhancement):
    The entire banner is wrapped in a <form> that POSTs to /cookies.
    The Accept and Reject buttons are <button type="submit"> elements
    with name="analytics" and value="true" or "false". When clicked
    without JS, the browser submits the form normally. The server
    processes the consent, sets the cookie, and redirects back to the
    page the user was on (via the hidden returnUrl input).

  HOW IT WORKS WITH JAVASCRIPT (enhanced experience):
    The client-side cookies.js script intercepts the button clicks,
    prevents the default form submission, and instead:
    1. Shows the accepted/rejected confirmation banner
    2. Immediately loads GTM (on accept) or deletes GA cookies (on reject)
    3. Sends an async XHR POST to /cookies to persist the choice
    4. Redirects back to the current page on success

    The data attributes on the banner container pass server-generated
    values to the client-side script:
    - data-crumb: the CSRF token for the XHR POST
    - data-gtm-key: the GTM container ID to load on acceptance
    - data-return-url: the page to redirect back to

  WHY BOTH MODES?
    GOV.UK services must work without JavaScript (WCAG 2.2, progressive
    enhancement). The form-based approach ensures basic functionality.
    JavaScript enhances the experience with instant feedback and no
    full-page reload.

  CSRF PROTECTION:
    The hidden crumb input is required for the form POST to succeed.
    Without it, @hapi/crumb would reject the submission with 403.
#}

{% from "govuk/components/cookie-banner/macro.njk" import govukCookieBanner %}

{% set questionHtml %}
  <p class="govuk-body">We use some essential cookies to make this service work.</p>
  <p class="govuk-body">We'd also like to use analytics cookies so we can understand how you use the service and make improvements.</p>
{% endset %}

{% set acceptedHtml %}
  <p class="govuk-body">You've accepted analytics cookies. You can <a class="govuk-link" href="/cookies">change your cookie settings</a> at any time.</p>
{% endset %}

{% set rejectedHtml %}
  <p class="govuk-body">You've rejected analytics cookies. You can <a class="govuk-link" href="/cookies">change your cookie settings</a> at any time.</p>
{% endset %}

<form action="/cookies" method="post" novalidate>
  <input type="hidden" name="crumb" value="{{ crumb }}">
  <input type="hidden" name="async" value="false">
  <input type="hidden" name="returnUrl" value="{{ currentPath }}">

  {{ govukCookieBanner({
    ariaLabel: "Cookies on " + serviceName,
    classes: "js-cookies-container js-cookies-banner",
    attributes: {
      "data-crumb": crumb,
      "data-gtm-key": googleTagManagerKey,
      "data-return-url": currentPath,
      "data-nosnippet": ""
    },
    messages: [
      {
        headingText: "Cookies on " + serviceName,
        html: questionHtml,
        classes: "js-question-banner",
        actions: [
          {
            text: "Accept analytics cookies",
            type: "submit",
            name: "analytics",
            value: "true",
            classes: "js-cookies-button-accept"
          },
          {
            text: "Reject analytics cookies",
            type: "submit",
            name: "analytics",
            value: "false",
            classes: "js-cookies-button-reject"
          },
          {
            text: "View cookies",
            href: "/cookies"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        html: acceptedHtml,
        role: "alert",
        hidden: true,
        classes: "js-cookies-accepted",
        actions: [
          {
            text: "Hide this message",
            type: "button",
            classes: "js-hide"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        html: rejectedHtml,
        role: "alert",
        hidden: true,
        classes: "js-cookies-rejected",
        actions: [
          {
            text: "Hide this message",
            type: "button",
            classes: "js-hide"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }) }}
</form>
